            <!-- ENGLISH VERSION OF OFFER 1 -->
            <div class="doc-content" data-lang="en">
                <p><strong>On entering into an agreement for the provision of software development services and the transfer of rights to the software</strong></p>
                <p>Date of publication: June 13, 2025</p>

                <h3>1. General Provisions</h3>
                <p>1.1. This Public Offer (hereinafter referred to as the "Offer") is an official offer by the Individual Developer PAT (hereinafter referred to as the "Contractor"), addressed to an indefinite number of persons (hereinafter referred to as the "Customer"), to enter into an agreement for the provision of software development services and/or the transfer of rights to the software (hereinafter referred to as the "Agreement") under the terms and conditions set forth in this Offer.</p>
                <p>1.2. In accordance with paragraph 2 of Article 437 of the Civil Code of the Russian Federation, this Offer is public. The Contractor undertakes to provide services and grant rights to use the software to any requesting Customer on equal terms.</p>
                <p>1.3. The Agreement is considered concluded (accepted) upon the Customer's completion of the implied actions stipulated in Section 2 of this Offer.</p>
                <p>1.4. By completing the implied actions, the Customer confirms that they have read, fully understood, and unconditionally accept all the terms of this Offer in full, without any exceptions or limitations (as defined by Article 428 of the Civil Code of the Russian Federation—an adhesion agreement).</p>

                <h3>2. Terms and Definitions</h3>
                <p>The following terms and definitions are used in this Offer:</p>
                <p><strong>Offer:</strong> This document, "Public Offer for the Conclusion of an Agreement for the Provision of Software Development Services and the Transfer of Rights to Software," with appendices, which form an integral part of it.</p>
                <p><strong>Implied Actions:</strong> The Customer's behavior expressing their consent to enter into the Agreement under the terms of the Offer. The actions consist of: (1) sending the Contractor a request for work through the contacts specified in Section 12, and (2) making a 100% advance payment in accordance with the procedure set forth in Section 6.</p>
                <p><strong>Contractor:</strong> An individual PAT developer granting rights to use the Software and providing development services.</p>
                <p><strong>Customer:</strong> An individual or legal entity that has accepted this Offer and acquired the rights to use the Software and/or services.</p>
                <p><strong>Software:</strong> The result of intellectual activity (source code, executable files, databases, interfaces) created by the Contractor in accordance with the Customer's Terms of Reference.</p>
                <p><strong>Terms of Reference:</strong> A document defining the functional requirements for the software, the deadlines, cost, and acceptance procedure, agreed upon by the Parties in simple written form (including messaging on Telegram).</p>
                <p><strong>Services:</strong> The Contractor's actions related to software development, transfer of exclusive rights, provision of technical support, and consulting.</p>

                <h3>3. Subject of the Agreement</h3>
                <p>3.1. The Contractor undertakes, at the Customer's request, to perform software development work and/or provide services (including technical support and consulting), and to transfer the rights to use the software to the Customer. The Customer undertakes to accept the result and pay for it in the manner stipulated by this Offer.</p>
                <p>3.2. Specific characteristics, functional requirements, deadlines, and cost are defined in the Terms of Reference (TOR), which become an integral part of the Agreement upon its signing by both Parties (including approval via instant messaging).</p>
                <p>3.3. All work, unless otherwise agreed, is performed by the Contractor personally.</p>

